# Force LF for all text files regardless of the checking-out machine's
# core.autocrlf setting. Without this, a Windows checkout with
# core.autocrlf=true silently rewrites LF -> CRLF on checkout, which
# breaks any test that compares extracted/rendered text byte-for-byte
# against a committed golden fixture (discovered: task 024's
# document-render golden-file tests, corrupted this way during a merge
# checkout even though the committed blobs were correctly LF).
* text=auto eol=lf
